OL,3,CSir Quentin Blake unveils mural ahead
OL,4,Cof illustration centre opening
OL,6,FThe drawing depicts a bridge over New
OL,7,FRiver, which has supplied water to
OL,8,FLondon since 1613.
OL,10,FThe mural is said to evoke the social
OL,11,Fhistory of the river and the long-
OL,12,Flasting relationship between people
OL,13,Fand water.
OL,15,FSir Quentin, 93, said: "I was
OL,16,Fespecially pleased to be asked to
OL,17,Fproduce a mural for Quentin Blake
OL,18,FCentre's cafe. You will see that I
OL,19,Fhave drawn a bridge. It does not
OL,20,Factually exist but I needed one to act
OL,21,Fas a bridge to the past.
OL,26,@wD@XOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
